lzz.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:67:{i:0;s:190:"Use quality garage door grease to lubricate the chain and sprocket on chain drive systems to the screw on screw drive system and to the lubrication points recommended on a belt drive system.";i:1;s:67:"It is also recommended that the trolley and rails the trolley ride.";i:2;s:100:"The most important part of the door to lubricate is the steel rollers which are located at each end.";i:3;s:163:"These should be greased with a heavy-duty lithium grease designed for garage doors as well as other industrial applications that require heavy duty metal surfaces.";i:4;s:65:"Its actually the garage door opener track that needs lubrication.";i:5;s:45:"Where to create the garage door opener track.";i:6;s:78:"Many people will apply lubrication spray to the bottom of your tracks service.";i:7;s:92:"When in reality the garage door openers trolly runs and grips down on the top of that track.";i:8;s:72:"This is where all the friction is and where any spray should be applied.";i:9;s:64:"Locate the torsion springs that lift and lower your garage door.";i:10;s:158:"This is one of the most important parts of a garage door to lubricate because lubricating the springs can increase their efficiency as well as their lifespan.";i:11;s:43:"Apply just enough to make them move better.";i:12;s:86:"Its crucial that you do not apply any solution to the bearings or tracks of your door.";i:13;s:124:"Grease Your Garage Door Hinges The hinges are attached to the back of the garage door both in the middle and along the side.";i:14;s:104:"Lock Although your lock may not squeak its best to keep it regularly lubricated so it does not seize up.";i:15;s:54:"Its also important to avoid using grease at all costs.";i:16;s:106:"Grease will create a stickiness thats hard to clean so it can lead to a faster buildup of damaging debris.";i:17;s:34:"Parts of Garage Door to Lubricate.";i:18;s:141:"Many parts of a garage door require frequent lubrication for smooth opening and closing operation which should be part of your self-designed.";i:19;s:83:"Spray the garage door lubricant at the pivot points unless you have plastic hinges.";i:20;s:95:"Plastic hinges dont need to be lubricated and in fact the lubricant can do more harm than good.";i:21;s:184:"Its important to avoid getting garage door lubricant on the tracks of your garage door as the grease can attract dirt and dust particles and interfere with the functioning of the door.";i:22;s:38:"We recommend simply wiping the tracks.";i:23;s:53:"Lubricating Genie Screw Garage Door Opener - YouTube.";i:24;s:80:"Once youve done this open and close the garage door to spread the grease around.";i:25;s:55:"You need to next lubricate the lock on the garage door.";i:26;s:78:"This makes it easier to lock and unlock and will prevent rust in the long run.";i:27;s:44:"Youll just need to spray the lubricant once.";i:28;s:45:"Exposed ball bearings need periodic greasing.";i:29;s:85:"Garage door pulleys and rollers may have bearings that require an annual lubrication.";i:30;s:52:"Lubricate a garage door to keep it working smoothly.";i:31;s:47:"Most doors squeak when they need to be greased.";i:32;s:99:"A once-a-year lubrication of all the moving parts is usually enough to keep the door in good shape.";i:33;s:48:"White Lithium Grease to lubricate a garage door.";i:34;s:117:"You can also spray white lithium grease on different parts of the garage door to make it work and roll more smoothly.";i:35;s:151:"WD-40 High-Performance White Lithium Grease provides great long-term lubrication and has a high viscosity formula which means that it wont drip or run.";i:36;s:80:"With all of these benefits it can reduce friction and wear for your garage door.";i:37;s:84:"Youll be applying the grease at the pivot points so youll want it to be free-moving.";i:38;s:98:"Starting at the top spray or apply your grease to the following parts attached to the door itself.";i:39;s:90:"As you work your way down raise the garage doo